# Firebase Patterns: HR-Lite

This rule defines how to handle Firebase services (Firestore, Auth, Storage) in HR-Lite.

## 📦 SDK Version
- Always use the **Modular SDK** (`firebase/auth`, `firebase/firestore`, `firebase/storage`).
- **DO NOT** use the legacy namespaced version (`firebase.auth()`).

## 🏗 Service Layers
- Place all Firestore queries and Auth calls in `src/services/`.
- Examples: `src/services/jobService.js`, `src/services/candidateService.js`.
- Components should only call these services, not the SDK directly.

## 🔍 Firestore Rules
- Be aware of the existing security rules (defined in `firestore.rules`).
- Use `where()`, `orderBy()`, and `limit()` to optimize queries.
- Prefer `onSnapshot()` for real-time dashboards and `getDoc()` for static pages.

## 📄 File Processing
- Upload files to Firebase Storage first.
- Save the storage URL/path in Firestore.
- Hand off processing (Mammoth, Gemini AI) to **Cloud Functions**.

## 🛡 Auth Flow
- Always use the `useAuth` custom hook (check `src/contexts/AuthContext.js`).
- Protect internal pages via the `DashboardLayout` or higher-level route guards.
